# Release notes (codeblock) + changelog

## Release notes must be in a codeblock

Whenever the user asks for **App Store release notes** / "What's New" copy,
output the final notes inside a single fenced **codeblock** so they can be copied
straight into App Store Connect's textarea. No commentary inside the block.

- Plain user language. No file paths, no spec section numbers (no `§11.6`), no
  internal jargon (no "focus platter", "UITextField", "peek").
- **Textarea-safe bullets:** prefix each line item with a literal `• ` (bullet +
  space). Do **not** use Markdown `-`/`*` bullets or blank-line-separated
  paragraphs in the codeblock — App Store Connect's textarea renders plain text,
  and `• ` pastes cleanly as a visible bullet.
- Short bullets, active voice ("New", "Now you can…", "Fixed").
- It's fine to add a one-line note *outside* the codeblock (e.g. offer a shorter
  variant); the copy-paste block itself stays clean.

## Keep `docs/CHANGELOG.md` current

`docs/CHANGELOG.md` is the source of truth for those release notes.

- Append a bullet under **`## [Unreleased]`** whenever a user-facing tvOS change
  ships (new feature, visible UI/UX change, user-noticeable bug fix). Group under
  **Added / Changed / Fixed**. Skip invisible changes (refactors, build/tooling,
  docs, tests).
- When the user cuts a version (e.g. "new version is 1.1.0"), rename
  `## [Unreleased]` to `## [<version>] — <YYYY-MM-DD>` and add a fresh empty
  `## [Unreleased]` block on top. Don't rewrite historical version sections.
- When asked for release notes for a version, pull them from that version's
  changelog section so the store copy and the changelog match.

## Scope

- tvOS app only. Backend changes live in `reversion/`; the mobile app has its own
  changelog in `reversion-app/docs/CHANGELOG.md`.
